IRS990.MissionDesc: TO ADVOCATE FOR EDUCATION PROFESSIONALS AND TO UNITE OUR MEMBERS, KANSANS, AND THE NATION TO FULFILL THE PROMISE OF PUBLIC EDUCATION TO PREPARE EVERY STUDENT TO SUCCEED IN A DIVERSE AND INTERDEPENDENT WORLD.
IRS990.Desc: THE UNISERV PROGRAM PROVIDES ASSISTANCE AND SUPPORT FOR THE MEMBERS AND AFFILIATES INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, ASSISTANCE WITH COLLECTIVE BARGAINING AND NEGOTIATIONS, CONTRACT ENFORCEMENT, PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT ACTIVITIES, PROFESSIONAL EDUCATION OPPORTUNITIES, MEMBER COMMUNICATIONS , AND MEMBER RECRUITMENT AND RETENTION.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: THE LEGAL SERVICES PROGRAM PROVIDES NEEDED LEGAL ASSISTANCE AND ADVICE TO MEMBERS AND AFFILIATES WITH REGARD TO LABOR RELATIONS, INDIVIDUAL RIGHTS, BARGAINING RIGHTS, CONTRACT ENFORCEMENT, AND OTHER MATTERS WITH LEGAL OR QUASI-LEGAL IMPLICATIONS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: THE COMMUNICATIONS PROGRAM PROVIDES INFORMATION TO MEMBERS, AFFILIATES, AND THE GENERAL PUBLIC ADVOCATING FOR PUBLIC EDUCATION AND FOR PUBLIC EDUCATORS THROUGH BROADCAST, PRINT, SOCIAL, AND WEB-BASED MEDIA. THIS PROGRAM ALSO WORKS WITH RELEVANT BUSINESS MEDIA AND POLITICAL LEADERS TO GARNER SUPPORT FOR AND TO PROMOTE PUBLIC EDUCATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: KEVIN RIEMANN, EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR, MADE $1,200 IN DEFERRED COMPENSATION PAYMENTS TO AN IRC SECTION 457 PLAN.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION INCLUDES AN AGENDA ITEM FOR REVIEW OF THE FORM 990 DURING THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS MEETING THAT OCCURS IMMEDIATELY AFTER THE COMPLETION OF THE FORM 990 EACH YEAR. GENERALLY, THAT MEETING OCCURS IN EARLY DECEMBER. THE DIRECTORS ARE PROVIDED WITH A COPY OF THE FORM 990 AND ALL SCHEDULES PRIOR TO THIS MEETING AND THEN ARE ENCOURAGED TO ASK ANY QUESTIONS OR VOICE ANY CONCERNS DURING THE BOARD MEETING DISCUSSIONS. AFTER THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS HAS REVIEWED THE FORM 990, IT IS THEN SIGNED BY THE PRESIDENT AND FILED WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION GATHERS INFORMATION FROM SIMILAR ORGANIZATIONS IN THE SAME GEOGRAPHIC REGION AND THE NATIONAL EDUCATION ASSOCIATION AND COMPARES COMPENSATION PACKAGES FOR THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR, THE ASSOCIATE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR, THE PRESIDENT, AND THE VICE PRESIDENT. THIS INFORMATION IS CONSIDERED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS WHEN DETERMINING THE SALARY AND COMPENSATION LEVELS FOR EACH OF THESE POSITIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, Line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE NOT AVAILABLE TO THE GENERAL PUBLIC DURING THE TAX YEAR.
